This paper is primarily focused on facial expression analysis, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models and domain adaptation techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of face datasets and image synthesis, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed approach in driver emotion recognition, which falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) category.
